name: Idris Ademuyiwa Adelakun
biography: Idris Ademuyiwa Adelakun, Ph.D., P.Eng., PMP, CPEM, SFC obtained his diploma from the Polytechnic Ibadan and B.Sc. from the University of Ibadan, Nigeria. He went on to complete his M.Sc. in biosystems engineering and a letter of accomplishment in supervisory management at the University of Manitoba. He received his Ph.D. in Leadership - Organizational Management from Carolina University, USA. He is a professional engineer, project manager and a transformational leader. He has over nine years of experience in a Canadian business organization.

name: Ryan Kochie
biography: Ryan Kochie is a father of four and has worked for nearly 20 years in the culinary industry, often in a leadership and supervisory role becoming a red seal chef. He helps to run various online support groups including founding the long standing Parents of Winnipeg (POWSA Village), a successful resource for Parents across the city to connect on-line and in person. He also administers the marketplace Buy/Sell Winnipeg to help small local businesses advertise their wares and services and give access to people to easily sell their used items to the community. He will apply those same leadership, communication, organizational, and management skills in city hall and our community to make our area safer, more active, and more engaged. His intent is to be able to actively listen and communicate to many of you on what your priorities are, being available and responding in a timely manner to the concerns of local residents. He will bring that same passion he brings for all his endeavours to council.

name: Christopher Clacio
biography: Born and Raised in Winnipeg, MB all his life, 30 and an only child raised by a single parent. One thing he wants to do on his bucket list in life is to travel across Canada. He is a "Civic Practitioner" and a "Policy Entrepreneur" who has an ambitious vision to run for the office of the mayor in 2014, 2018, 2022, 2026 and 2030.He is no slouch in civic elections. He ran for school trustee in 7 Oaks School Division for ward 2 in 2014. In 2018, he also ran for mayor. On May 1st, 2022 he officially registered his campaign. His 4 key topics of engagement for citizens of Winnipeg are regional coordination, system change, civic innovation, and reasonable government.Since October 11, 2012 almost 10 years and going has been working in a grocery store in the Maples, where he lives. Over the years a colleague and he started an organization called Intercivics. Which is a citizen based group that educates on civics.He participated in the Next Up Leadership program in 2015-2016 which is a national leadership program for young leaders ages 18-32 who are committed to social, economic and environmental justice.
